ZH: 他们决定不介入这个争议。
EN: They decided not to intervene in the dispute.

ZH: 我们需要一个介入这个项目的专家。
EN: We need an expert to intervene in this project.

ZH: 政府介入了经济危机的解决。
EN: The government intervened in solving the economic crisis.

ZH: 医生立即介入救治伤者。
EN: The doctor immediately intervened to treat the injured.

ZH: 他的父母常常介入他的决策。
EN: His parents often intervene in his decisions.

ZH: 警察必须介入处理这个暴力冲突。
EN: The police must intervene in handling this violent conflict.

ZH: 我们需要一个公正的法官介入这个案件。
EN: We need a fair judge to intervene in this case.

ZH: 国际社会应该介入和平磋商，以解决这个战争。
EN: The international community should intervene in peace talks to resolve this war.

ZH: 我不会介入你们的争论。
EN: I will not intervene in your argument.

ZH: 你没有权利介入我的私人生活。
EN: You have no right to intervene in my private life.

ZH: 他的朋友劝他不要介入这个争端。
EN: His friends advised him not to get involved in this dispute.

ZH: 她的意见常常介入公司的决策。
EN: Her opinions often intervene in the company's decisions.

ZH: 条约禁止任何外国介入我们的内政。
EN: The treaty prohibits any foreign intervention in our internal affairs.

ZH: 总统决定介入这个危机以保护公民。
EN: The president decided to intervene in this crisis to protect the citizens.

ZH: 教师必须及时介入学生之间的冲突。
EN: Teachers must intervene promptly in conflicts between students.

ZH: 这个组织专门介入环境保护的问题。
EN: This organization specializes in intervening in environmental protection issues.

ZH: 她的干预很关键，才让这个计划成功。
EN: Her intervention was crucial for the success of this plan.

ZH: 随着父母的介入，孩子的学业有了显著改善。
EN: With the parents' intervention, the child's academic performance has significantly improved.

ZH: 这位名人决定介入这个慈善项目以帮助需要帮助的人们。
EN: The celebrity decided to get involved in this charity project to help those in need.

ZH: 这件事情已经超出了我们能介入的范围。
EN: This matter has already exceeded the scope in which we can intervene.
